post_text:
Bulldog Back to School Plan - Good Afternoon PAS Students and Families,

Please see the link below for details regarding the opening of school at both school buildings. This information will be reviewed at the school board meeting on Tuesday, August 25th prior to determining the school model for the start of the 2020-2021 school year. My recommendation for the board of education will be to start the school year with in-person learning for the elementary school and hybrid learning for the secondary school. Regardless of which building your child(ren) attends, all families have the option of selecting full-time remote learning for their child(ren). The District will review Covid-19 case data every two weeks to determine if a new learning model needs to be implemented. The initial learning model will be in place through September 25, 2020.

Stay Well,
Matt Bullard http://edne.tw/n657406

Dangers of Vaping Community Wide Presentation - PLEASE JOIN US FOR A COMMUNITY-WIDE PRESENTATION ON DANGERS OF VAPING
When: Tuesday, November 19
Time: 6:00 - 7:30
Where: Paynesville Area High School Auditorium
The Statewide Health Improvement Partnership through Stearns County Public Health focuses on areas of tobacco free living and health education. In order to address the epidemic of e-cig use and vaping in our community, SHIP will be presenting to the Paynesville Community on the trends of E-cigs and Vaping, What are e-cigs, what do we know about them, and why we should be concerned.
http://edne.tw/n598909

Bulldog State Football - Community Fan Bus Information - Paynesville Bulldogs VS. Minneapolis North at The Bank
Bus #1 will leave at 11:00 AM from the Paynesville Area Center
Bus #2 will leave at 11:15 AM from the Paynesville Area Center
Bus #3 will leave at 11:30 AM from the Paynesville Area Center - We are still working on lining this bus up.

Game Tickets are available online at ticketmaster.com or at the gate. Adult game tickets are $16 and students are $10

All students under the age of 16 must be chaperoned by an adult 21 or over.
Over flow parking for the Paynesville Area Center is available in the back gravel parking area at Subway.
Please arrive 10 minutes prior to departure time.
*We reserve the right to cancel any bus that does not reach our minimum occupancy. We will cancel by 12:00 PM on Wednesday November 13th. http://edne.tw/n598571

shared_text:
Evergreen Acres Dairy LLC
May 23, 2019 at 3:47 PM ·

Its always fun telling our dairy story! Today we hosted the Paynesville Area Schools 2nd grade class for a day on the farm. The kids got to see all the different parts of our farm and learn about cows and all the things we do to make our cows happy. It's such a rewarding experience teaching the younger generations.

Thanks to everyone who helped make this happen! Especially, @mirandabreth and the Stearns County Dairy Princesses and Ambassadors as well as @chelseaschossow and Form-A-Feed for sharing their knowledge about cows and the nutritious product they make. Also, Associated Milk Producers Inc for the cheese sticks!

FFA Region Awards! - Congratulations to our chapter members for a great year as it was recapped at our Region 3 FFA Banquet last night!

The chapter & members took home a total of 10 plaques for the event.
Eliza Carlson competed in the Region Talent contest and sang "The Climb." She got 1st and will be advancing on to state. Megan Laughlin did the chapter scrapbook and got 2nd, this event is only at the region level and not for state. Maggie Molitor was elected as the Vice President and Megan Ratka was elected the Sentinel for the Region 3 FFA Officers. http://edne.tw/n563355

post_text:
German Trip Update! - DAY 4: MARCH 28, 2019
What a great day in Munich! We started with our local guide Anita who showed us BMW World and then the Nymphenburg Palace, birthplace of Mad King Ludwig the II. Next we explored Germany's most famous beer hall the Hofbrauhaus and made it to Marienplatz in time for the Glockenspiel. The gang had a couple of hours free time to visit churches, and eat local street food before hopping back on the bus to visit Dachau, the former concentration camp. Of all of our visits, Dachau is the most moving and dark. All of the students were very attentive and respectful of this tragic and painful history. On our way to dinner in Munich, we jumped out of the bus to watch surfers enduring the cold in an off-shoot of the river Isar. For dinner we were as German as can be, eating bratwurst and mash, followed by apple strudel! http://edne.tw/n562006

post_text: On Thursday, January 31st, Paynesville Area Schools will open three hours late. The elementary school will begin at 11:00 a.m. and the secondary school will begin at 11:15. There will be no AM or PM preschool or preschool plus on Thursday, January 31st. Both schools will be serving lunch to all students on Thursday, January 31st. In the event that weather conditions worsen in the morning an additional message will be sent out to all families. Thank you for your patience, it is greatly appreciated.

Senator Jeff Howe
January 17, 2019 at 3:48 PM ·

Had the pleasure of meeting newly elected Paynesville School Board member Jacob Holck and Paynesville Area Schools Superintendent Matt Bullard today as we discussed education priorities for ISD 741.

Thank you both for your commitment to the young minds of our district!
